Ahead of decisive Qatar 2022 FIFA World Cup play-off against Super Eagles in March, Black Stars coach Otto Addo has reportedly travelled from his Dortmund base in Germany to London in order to hold talks with members of his backroom staff and some England-based players. Last Wednesday, the GFA named the Borussia Dortmund talent coach to lead a new technical team which includes compatriots George Boateng and Mas-Ud Didi Dramani as assistants, while Irish-Ghanaian coach, Chris Hughton, plays the role of technical advisor for two-leg playoff.   Nigeria gets continental approval for fencing academy     NSSF holds trials ahead of World School Athletics     Djokovic tops latest ATP rankings   The Graphic Sports claimed Addo jetted off to England last week for discussions with Hughton and Boateng, as well as some key players such Jordan Ayew, Thomas Partey, Andy Yiadom, Baba Rahman, among others, about the upcoming assignment. “I can confirm that the GFA facilitated talks between Otto Addo, the players and members of his technical team and so far things are going on smoothly,” a GFA official told the Graphic Sports . SPONSORED